SIMPLE: peradventure
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peradventure
<hw>Per`ad*ven"ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv. & conj.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>per aventure</ets>, F. <ets>par aventure</ets>. See <er>Per</er>,
and <er>Adventure</er>.]</ety> <def>By chance; perhaps; it may be; if;
supposing.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧If <xex>peradventure</xex> he speak against
me.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Peradventure</qex> there be fifty righteous within the
city.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xviii. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peradventure</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Peradventure
<hw>Per`ad*ven"ture</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Chance; hap; hence, doubt;
question; <as>as, proved beyond <ex>peradventure</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peraeopod</ent>⟦br⟧
